main event: On August 9 or 12, 1956, a bright object was observed floating or hovering overhead in Camden, Alabama, and Panama City, Florida.
interesting points: The object was observed at approximately 55 degrees elevation,It emitted sparkling or glittering light,The sighting lasted between 20 to 40 minutes,Local naval office determined that it could not have been a balloon,Evaluation suggested the object might be astronomical, possibly being the star Vega.
witness description: Civilian observations, no specific witnesses confirmed
